# State Management & Processing Status

## Core Approach

- Clear separation between processing completion and result existence
- Smart status detection with fallback logic
- Real-time updates via Supabase subscriptions
- Consistent status representation across UI components

## Processing Status Patterns

### Status Flag Semantics
```typescript
// Distinguish between "processing done" vs "results found"
interface ProcessingStatus {
  is_upload_done: boolean;         // File uploaded successfully
  is_ortho_done: boolean;          // Image processing completed
  is_metadata_done: boolean;       // Metadata extraction completed
  is_cog_done: boolean;            // Format optimization completed
  is_deadwood_done: boolean;       // AI analysis completed (regardless of results)
  has_error: boolean;              // Processing failed
  current_status: string;          // Current processing stage
}
```

### Smart Completion Detection
```typescript
// Handle edge cases where status flags don't reflect actual completion
function isProcessingActuallyComplete(dataset: ProcessingStatus): boolean {
  // Direct completion check
  if (dataset.is_field_done) return true;
  
  // Smart fallback: infer completion from overall state
  return !!(
    dataset.is_previous_steps_done &&
    dataset.current_status === 'idle' &&
    !dataset.has_error
  );
}
```

### Processing Progress Calculation
```typescript
// From src/utils/processingSteps.ts pattern
export function calculateProcessingProgress(dataset: DatasetProgress): ProgressResult {
  const stepCompletions = [
    dataset.is_upload_done || false,
    dataset.is_ortho_done || false,
    dataset.is_metadata_done || false,
    dataset.is_cog_done || false,
    isSmartCompletionCheck(dataset), // Smart detection for edge cases
  ];

  const currentStep = stepCompletions.findIndex(completed => !completed);
  const isComplete = currentStep === -1;

  return {
    currentStep: isComplete ? totalSteps : currentStep + 1,
    totalSteps,
    percentage: Math.round((stepCompletions.filter(Boolean).length / totalSteps) * 100),
    isComplete,
    currentStepInfo: PROCESSING_STEPS[isComplete ? totalSteps - 1 : currentStep]
  };
}
```

## Real-time State Synchronization

### Supabase Subscription Pattern
```typescript
// From src/hooks/useDatasetSubscription.ts
useEffect(() => {
  const channel = supabase
    .channel("status_changes")
    .on("postgres_changes", {
      event: "*",
      schema: "public", 
      table: "v2_statuses"
    }, async (payload) => {
      // Process status change
      const statusData = payload.new as StatusPayloadData;
      
      // Validate user ownership
      const { data: datasetInfo } = await supabase
        .from("v2_datasets")
        .select("user_id, file_name")
        .eq("id", statusData.dataset_id)
        .single();
        
      if (session?.user?.id !== datasetInfo.user_id) return;
      
      // Check for completion state changes
      const wasComplete = checkWasComplete(payload.old);
      const isNowComplete = checkIsComplete(payload.new);
      
      // Invalidate queries and show notifications
      await queryClient.invalidateQueries(["userDatasets", session.user.id]);
      
      if (!wasComplete && isNowComplete) {
        showProcessingCompleteNotification(datasetInfo.file_name, statusData.dataset_id);
      }
    })
    .subscribe();

  return () => supabase.removeChannel(channel);
}, [queryClient, session]);
```

### Query Invalidation Strategy
```typescript
// Selective invalidation based on completion state
if (isProcessingComplete) {
  // Update global data when processing completes
  await queryClient.invalidateQueries(["datasets"]);
  await queryClient.invalidateQueries(["authors"]);
} else {
  // Update only user-specific data during processing
  await queryClient.invalidateQueries(["userDatasets", userId]);
}
```

## UI Status Representation

### Processing Progress Component
```typescript
// From src/components/ProcessingProgress.tsx pattern
const ProcessingProgress: React.FC<{dataset: DatasetProgress}> = ({ dataset }) => {
  const progress = calculateProcessingProgress(dataset);
  
  // Error state
  if (dataset.has_error) {
    return <Tag icon={<CloseCircleOutlined />} color="error">Error</Tag>;
  }
  
  // Completion state
  if (progress.isComplete) {
    return <Tag icon={<CheckCircleOutlined />} color="success">Complete</Tag>;
  }
  
  // Processing state
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <span>Step {progress.currentStep} of {progress.totalSteps}</span>
      <ProgressBar percentage={progress.percentage} />
      <SyncOutlined spin />
    </div>
  );
};
```

### Status-Based Actions
```typescript
// Enable/disable actions based on processing state
const isComplete = calculateProcessingProgress(dataset).isComplete;

<Button 
  disabled={!isComplete}
  onClick={handleAction}
>
  {isComplete ? "Publish" : "Processing..."}
</Button>
```

## Common State Issues & Solutions

### Issue: Stuck Processing Spinners
**Symptom**: UI shows processing but work is actually done
**Cause**: Status flags don't reflect completion (especially for "no results found" cases)
**Solution**: Smart completion detection with fallback logic

```typescript
function isDeadwoodProcessingComplete(dataset: DatasetProgress): boolean {
  if (dataset.is_deadwood_done) return true;
  
  // Fallback: if all other steps done + idle + no error = completed
  return !!(
    dataset.is_upload_done &&
    dataset.is_ortho_done &&
    dataset.is_metadata_done &&
    dataset.is_cog_done &&
    !dataset.has_error &&
    dataset.current_status === 'idle'
  );
}
```

### Issue: Inconsistent Status Across Components
**Symptom**: Different components show different processing states
**Cause**: Multiple status calculation logics
**Solution**: Centralized status calculation utility

```typescript
// Single source of truth for status calculation
export { calculateProcessingProgress } from 'src/utils/processingSteps';

// Use consistently across all components
const progress = calculateProcessingProgress(dataset);
```

### Issue: Real-time Updates Not Working
**Symptom**: UI doesn't update when processing completes
**Cause**: Missing query invalidation or subscription errors
**Solution**: Comprehensive subscription handling with error boundaries

```typescript
// Robust subscription with error handling
.on("postgres_changes", { ... }, async (payload) => {
  try {
    // Process status change
    await handleStatusChange(payload);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Subscription error:", error);
    // Fallback: manual refresh
    await queryClient.invalidateQueries(["userDatasets"]);
  }
})
```

